io.simplesource.saga.client.dsl

Class SagaDSL.SagaBuilder<A>

  • java.lang.Object
    • io.simplesource.saga.client.dsl.SagaDSL.SagaBuilder<A>
  • Type Parameters:
    A - a representation of an action command that is shared across all actions in the saga. This is typically a generic type, such as Json, or if using Avro serialization, SpecificRecord or GenericRecord
    Enclosing class:
    SagaDSL

    public static final class SagaDSL.SagaBuilder<A>
extends Object
    A SagaBuilder is used to add actions by creating a subsaga consisting of a single action, and to build the saga once the definition steps are complete.

      • build

        public io.simplesource.data.Result<SagaError,Saga<A>> build()
        builds the Saga from all the subsagas that were previously defined by creating single actions with addAction and by defining the dependencies between these actions.

        The Saga returned can be considered an immutable data structure. Any mutations to saga state from this point on will result in a new instance being created.

        Returns:
        the result, either successful with the built Saga, or a SagaError.
